        "evidence": "<p><span>RBC replacement volume = RBC volume &times; ln (HbS, initial / HbS, goal) / donor Hct</span></p>\n<p><span>Where RBC volume = <calculator id=\"4065\">total blood volume</calculator> &times; patient Hct</span></p>\n<p><span>Note: HbS and Hct are in whole % (i.e., 30%, not 0.3).&nbsp;RBC units assume 350 mL per unit and are rounded up to the nearest whole unit.</span></p>",
